{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17588355","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17588355"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T09:06:26+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T09:06:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15129"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15129","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15129"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,1,0,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7817"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66831"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7817","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7817"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15129"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52285"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"14"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"36"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"152"},{"type":"tags","id":"1061"},{"type":"tags","id":"1291"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"6376"},{"type":"tags","id":"6442"},{"type":"tags","id":"7882"},{"type":"tags","id":"8115"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19057"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19060"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22330"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66831","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66831"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 32-year-old woman presents to the emergency department with symptoms that add up to a diagnosis of acute pyelonephritis.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best represents her likely symptoms?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Dysuria and frequency without systemic symptoms","Fever and flank pain with variable urinary symptoms","Gradual onset of malaise over several weeks","Suprapubic pain without fever","Suprapubic pain and dysuria"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EAcute pyelonephritis typically presents with \u003Cstrong\u003Efever and flank pain with variable urinary symptoms\u003C/strong\u003E. The presentation can range from mild to severe, but usually includes fever \u0026gt;38\u00b0C and unilateral or bilateral flank pain. Lower urinary tract symptoms like \u003Cstrong\u003Edysuria and frequency without systemic symptoms\u003C/strong\u003E are more typical of simple cystitis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnlike the \u003Cstrong\u003Egradual onset of malaise over several weeks\u003C/strong\u003E seen in chronic conditions, pyelonephritis usually has an acute onset. \u003Cstrong\u003ESuprapubic pain without fever \u003C/strong\u003Ewould be very non-specific and these symptoms alone would not be sufficient to make a diagnosis of acute pyelonephritis.\u003Cstrong\u003E \u003C/strong\u003E \u003Cstrong\u003ESuprapubic pain and dysuria\u003C/strong\u003E would be unusual and more characteristic of lower urinary tract infection.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe most common causative organism is \u003Cem\u003EEscherichia coli\u003C/em\u003E, accounting for approximately 80% of cases.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Acute pyelonephritis typically presents with fever, flank pain, and variable lower urinary tract symptoms","The most common causative organism in acute pyelonephritis is \u003Cem\u003EEscherichia coli\u003C/em\u003E","Lower urinary tract symptoms in pyelonephritis can range from absent to severe"],"references":["Sabih A, Leslie SW. Complicated Urinary Tract Infections. 2023 Nov 12. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 28613784","Bilsen MP, Jongeneel RMH, Schneeberger C, Platteel TN, van Nieuwkoop C, Mody L, Caterino JM, Geerlings SE, K\u00f6ves B, Wagenlehner F, Conroy SP, Visser LG, Lambregts MMC. Definitions of Urinary Tract Infection in Current Research: A Systematic Review. Open Forum Infect Dis. 2023 Jun 27;10(7):ofad332. doi: 10.1093/ofid/ofad332. PMID: 37426954; PMCID: PMC10323732","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52285"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15129"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52285","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52285"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-02T15:41:23+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-02T15:42:05+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7817"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66831"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"14","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/14"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udda0","name":"Infectious Diseases","synonyms":["ID"],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2021-05-21T07:51:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\